200
00:15:35,129 --> 00:15:37,639
It's already over. I went
as soon as I got here to Tokyo.

201
00:15:37,639 --> 00:15:38,629
Then what happened?

202
00:15:38,629 --> 00:15:41,109
Then, I will wait for the results back home.

203
00:15:41,109 --> 00:15:44,809
If it's not metastatic cancer, there's no
need for anti-cancer agents.

204
00:15:44,909 --> 00:15:48,079
It's bad if you don't tell Marilyn such
an important thing.

205
00:15:48,109 --> 00:15:52,779
Until now, I've always lived my life selfishly,
I don't want to rely on her at this late stage.

206
00:15:52,919 --> 00:15:54,149
Here you go.

207
00:15:57,309 --> 00:15:58,419
This...

208
00:16:00,789 --> 00:16:04,059
After Marilyn saw this...

209
00:16:05,629 --> 00:16:13,329
...it brought back memories of how
you made this often for her.

210
00:16:15,149 --> 00:16:17,039
I wonder if such a taste...

211
00:16:17,629 --> 00:16:20,409
...is something she has never forgotten.

212
00:16:32,819 --> 00:16:35,519
Has Mari-chan been here?

213
00:16:36,309 --> 00:16:37,229
Nope.

214
00:16:37,869 --> 00:16:44,269
I see. There's something I want
to apologize to her for.

215
00:16:46,549 --> 00:16:49,939
Well, her mother just left a while ago...

216
00:16:50,629 --> 00:16:53,939
She's headed to the station,
and will be going home today.

217
00:16:54,349 --> 00:16:55,639
Is that so...

218
00:17:07,349 --> 00:17:09,219
Eri-san, I...

219
00:17:10,469 --> 00:17:13,889
Chuu-san, I really want to thank you.

220
00:17:15,182 --> 00:17:20,012
I got to see Mariko, and
see that she's doing fine...

221
00:17:20,994 --> 00:17:23,594
It's all thanks to you.

222
00:17:24,589 --> 00:17:28,639
I was just some drunk guy.

223
00:17:30,749 --> 00:17:31,739
Take care of yourself.

224
00:17:32,509 --> 00:17:36,019
Oh, right. Why don't you come
and visit me next time!

225
00:17:41,809 --> 00:17:43,259
Kimi-kun...

226
00:17:48,155 --> 00:17:51,435
Marilyn-san, flowers for you.

227
00:17:51,522 --> 00:17:52,454
Huh?

228
00:17:52,669 --> 00:17:55,069
Oh... put it there.

229
00:17:55,808 --> 00:17:58,758
It's ten minutes before show time.
See you later.

230
00:17:58,843 --> 00:17:59,853
Okay.

231
00:18:07,162 --> 00:18:13,002
[At least, take care of your body. I may be
an incompetent mother but I wish for us
to be mother and daughter until the end. ~Mom]

232
00:18:16,309 --> 00:18:17,659
What's this about?

233
00:18:17,659 --> 00:18:18,889
It's from your mom.

234
00:18:19,269 --> 00:18:20,489
I already know that.

235
00:18:21,349 --> 00:18:25,669
Master of Meshi-ya had informed me, that
your mom was going back home this morning.

236
00:18:25,749 --> 00:18:28,139
Then I went to see her off.

237
00:18:28,429 --> 00:18:30,269
You didn't have to do that!

238
00:18:30,269 --> 00:18:35,779
The truth is your mom came to Tokyo, in order
to have a precise check-up at a university hospital.

239
00:18:38,989 --> 00:18:44,619
But, since she didn't want to trouble you,
she lied to you by saying she was here on a sight-seeing trip.

240
00:18:45,909 --> 00:18:51,649
Then she gave me money
to buy you some flowers.

241
00:18:54,629 --> 00:18:58,269
Your mom lowered her head to me...

242
00:18:59,069 --> 00:19:04,409
...she said "Please take care of Mariko"
and bowed her head over and over.

243
00:19:09,069 --> 00:19:11,279
She's such a fool.

244
00:19:13,189 --> 00:19:16,379
I will accept...

245
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:18,209
...everything about you.

246
00:19:18,589 --> 00:19:22,719
<i>"Next up is Marilyn-san..."</i>

247
00:19:23,029 --> 00:19:25,379
Marilyn-san, it's your turn.

248
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:26,590
Okay.

249
00:19:45,580 --> 00:19:50,920
<i>Results from the precise check-up seem
to show no findings of metastatic cancer.</i>

250
00:19:52,336 --> 00:19:57,136
<i>Then a month later,
Eri-san got married.</i>

251
00:20:00,029 --> 00:20:05,429
<i>I heard that only the bride and groom, Marilyn
and the rest of these people were at the ceremony but still...</i>

252
00:20:05,429 --> 00:20:09,039
<i>...Eri-san was very happy.</i>

253
00:20:10,029 --> 00:20:14,909
What's with this pouty face, Marilyn
at such a happy occasion.

254
00:20:14,909 --> 00:20:16,439
They fought again.

255
00:20:16,749 --> 00:20:19,409
It's because she said my clothes look miserly.

256
00:20:19,519 --> 00:20:22,329
Then, her mom said,
"You'd look better naked."

257
00:20:24,999 --> 00:20:26,469
Thanks for waiting.

258
00:20:29,179 --> 00:20:31,209
I'm digging in.

259
00:20:40,719 --> 00:20:42,319
Was it like you had in the past?

260
00:20:44,459 --> 00:20:47,789
Your mother had taught me her recipe.

261
00:21:02,319 --> 00:21:07,379
I had wanted to eat
my mom's Cabbage Rolls.

262
00:21:29,549 --> 00:21:33,949
When making in advance, do it like this
so it will be easier to roll.

263
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:36,719
Handle it delicately and with great feeling.

264
00:21:36,719 --> 00:21:39,979
It's bad if you don't treat women like that.

265
00:21:41,353 --> 00:21:47,073
When you place them in the soup, don't touch
them while they're cooking or else they will crumble.

266
00:21:47,151 --> 00:21:49,141
So then, good night.

